fields: The words of the man who was my dad...
Even if I was a mistake from the beginning, the path I've chosen isn't.
I wanted that event to be more than just a tragic backstory.
That's why I yearned to become a champion of justice.
For over ten years, I've clung to the ideal
of a world where everyone is happy and no one needs to cry.
So it was clear from the beginning what I needed to do.
I didn't fight because I became a Master.
I decided to fight because it was something that I could do.
Something I believed I ought to do.
You can continue to defy me all you like, but your Servant body cannot resist me.
Surely you can sense my Command Spells eating away at you, little by little.
Would it not be easier if you simply gave in and submitted to me?
I'd like a girl like you.
With gold hair, a small body, young and noble-minded like a boy.
It is admirable that you choose death over betrayal.
I really want to trample on you.
I will make you become my Servant of your own will.
Not your body, but I will start by breaking down your heart.
I thought I requested for you to remain at Ryuudou Temple.
Yesterday, I seized the Servant of Emiya Shirou,  one of the other Masters.
He escaped just before I could finish him,  but he is no longer a Master.
I see. But I do not remember instructing you to do so.
I acted on my own authority, Master.
I attacked this church in order to obtain the Holy Grail's vessel
and slew the priest who oversaw it, but the Grail's whereabouts remain unknown.
You failed to return because you couldn't locate the Grail?
I get the gist of the situation.
Now, can you explain why you acted on your own?
However, my actions were all for your sake, Master.
My only goal is to help you achieve victory.
In that case, you cannot leave this place.
Search it until you are satisfied.
Until then, I will also remain here.
No, that will not be necessary, Master.
Locating the Holy Grail will take some time.
It would be safer for you to return to Ryuudou Temple.
But if I did so, I would be unable to achieve my own objective.
Be quick about it. If the Grail isn't here, so be it.
I don't care how you accomplish this task. All I need is the result.
When was it that I finally figured out the true nature of that dream?
That it was a certain Heroic Spirit's mental landscape.
Among the many Heroic Spiritsthe Servants
there are special Servants that are safeguards, called "Guardians."
They are summoned into the various ages  and prevent the human world's destruction.
Or, more accurately, they counter the human race's self-destruction.
Even though he was summoned to save humanity, before he could save them, he was forced to shoulder their countless mistakes.
It didn't take long for him to determine that it was futile and start despising the human world.
In the end, he continued to be betrayed by his ideal, even after death.
If you aren't feeling well, we can put this off.
There's no pressing need to attack right away.
No, if we know where Caster is, we should deal with her at once.
So you just watched me sleep instead of waking me? That's kinda creepy.
Relax. I wouldn't dream of doing something so improper.
I did overhear a thing or two, though.
You muttered a few rather harsh things, like "This is so irritating" and "I'm pissed."
Have you ever regretted the things you've done?
I want to do whatever I can to avoid having regrets.
That's probably easier said than done, though.
I bet it's even harder than I imagine.
Some can do it, and some can't.
You strike me as the former type.
Not only do such people rarely make mistakes, they don't dwell on the ones they do.
Brilliant people shine more brightly than ordinary ones.
They never regret or agonize over what they've done.
And you are most definitely that sort of person.
Tohsaka Rin can believe in her own path to the very end without regret.
Will you be able to believe you made the right choices until the very end?
I'm sorry, but that question is meaningless.
My "end" came and went long ago.
Jeez... Where the heck has she gone to?
Think hard about where she is likely to go!
I don't have time to cherry-pick.
He's the only person she can rely on.
She attacked the overseer? I'd say that's a bold move.
Kirei was probably prepared for it, though.
Rin, I must ask you again.
If you get too close, she might use Rule Breaker on you too.
So I'll leave her Master, Kuzuki, to you.
I'm fine with taking on that man.
But do you understand that no mage alive is a match for Caster?
Relax. If I didn't have a chance, I wouldn't have suggested it.
You can leave her to me, Archer.
Very well. I'll believe in you.
I'll take out Caster here, no matter what.
And when I do, Saber will probably return to normal and be able to forge a new pact with Shirou, right?
Seemed like he was not going to give me the Grail without protesting.
So, did you make sure he was dead?
And what is that supposed to mean?
If you didn't see his corpse, he's still stubbornly clinging to life somewhere. That's all.
But enough about him. Let's get this over with.
This time, you don't have a human shield, so I can go all out to beat you.
Do you think you can beat me in a battle of magic?
It depends on how I go about it.
And thankfully, you don't seem to have full control of Saber yet.
Plus, I also know how strong Kuzuki-sensei is.
He's no match for my Archer.
We proceed as planned, then, Rin?
Don't hold back. I'm using everything I have!
You think you have a chance against me one-on-one?
Are you forgetting my trump card?
With my Command Spells, I can make her my puppet here and now.
Were you to use one, Saber would be able to resist it.
I don't know if it would be for one minute or two, but that's more than enough time to take down the likes of you!
I'll start by dragging you down to Earth!
What do you think you're doing, Archer?
You see, defeating her here struck me as overly idealistic.
When it comes to escaping, she's the best there is.
She even tore apart her own younger brother to get away.
You talk as though you know all about me.
Have you discerned my true identity?
Familiars that use dragon teeth as vessels are the hallmark of the King of Colchis's magic.
His daughter, Princess Medea, was hailed as a witch without peer.
If I may ask, Caster, do you still have reserves to spare?
I've stored sufficient mana to sustain  not only one more but all the Servants!
I will take you up on your earlier offer, Caster.
Even though you turned me down before?
Considering the advantage that Saber confers, isn't it only natural that I should side with you?
I'm only yielding to you for my own benefit.
There is no trust or loyalty in that.
But is that not how Servants are by nature?
I suppose I wouldn't be much of a mage if I couldn't keep you under control.
Thus, I shall play into your hands.
What do you think you're doing?
So that appears to be that.
Though I did not expect your rude interruption, the outcome remains unchanged.
I want to attach one condition to my joining your forces.
I offered my freedom without resistance.
My price is that you let them leave.
For all your words and actions, you're rather soft.
No. I merely thought it would be wrong for a Heroic Spirit
to cut down his heartbroken former Master.
It's strange to hear common decency from a traitor's mouth.
Very well. I shall let them go.
But if they ever get in my way again...
Fools who would embrace a hopeless fight deserve to be cut down without mercy.
Let's go. For now, he's right.
Any anger you might hold for me is misplaced, Rin.
This woman is simply the superior Master. That's all.
I side with the most powerful.
You hear me? I'll defeat Caster and take you back.
And when I do, no amount of apology will be enough.
That's what you get for pulling a stunt like that!
No, let's get back to my place as soon as possible.
You can't be serious! Don't tell me it doesn't hurt, not with an injury like that!
Couldn't you tell right away that the church wasn't safe?
I'm not that stupid. Of course I could!
Then you should have turned right around, idiot!
How could you try projecting with those injuries?
You should've known it'd just make them worse!
And now you're telling me you aren't in pain?
Well, you're hurting worse than I am, right?
You can gripe and moan once we get back.
I can't believe this. A guy made me cry.
Shut up. You're going to make this right, jerk.
Listen, don't you dare turn around.
If you see my face, I'll get really mad.
I should have defeated Caster  when I had the chance, no matter what it took.
I'm not whining or anything, but I always mess up the most important thing.
I can handle the second or third most important thing easily.
But I always mess up the most important one.
I can't only blame him for going over to her side.
Sheesh. After all I said, I suddenly found myself cornered.
I think this is where you're supposed to say, "By what?"
By you. Your words made me realize I'd failed,  and I got even more depressed.
You haven't done anything to beat yourself up over.
We're in this mess because my strategy was so wrong.
That just means you failed at one thing.
But that doesn't mean you're wrong, Tohsaka.
To be honest, you look blindingly brilliant to me.
I believe what I've done to be right, but...
That belief is a mess of patches.
But once you get that regret out of your system, I bet you'll pay them back twice over.
By the way, why did you save me?
Huh? How did you get that?
I have another pendant just like it at my house.
After Lancer nearly killed me at school, I found it lying next to me. I've had it ever since.
You have one just like it?
Huh? Did I say something strange?
Anyway, why would this be a reason for you to save me?
The truth is, that was an afterthought.
If I must confess, I've always been attracted to this girl named Tohsaka Rin.
When I finally got around to talking to her, I fell for her even more.
So before I knew it, I had already  jumped down there without thinking.
H-Hey, if you go around blurting out things like that without thinking, people will get the wrong idea!
I really do have feelings for you!
Thanks for coming to my rescue.
I appreciate your thoughtfulness, but before that...
It works best when the raw materials are fresh.
Could we work with other Masters?
You are about to die here, so is that any of your concern?
Can't come up with decent ideas on an empty stomach, right?
I did a lot of thinking afterward.
About why I started fighting in the Grail War.
About what I wanted to accomplish.
At first it was just because I got dragged into it,  but that makes no difference.
I like champions of justice,  and I want to follow their example.
So I have to protect people.
Master or not, Saber or not...
I'm going to fight all the same.
Look, this is serious. At least pay attention.
The idea of others dying bothers you more than the idea of your own death.
So you've decided to keep fighting despite your weakness, right?
What's with you? You look like a squirrel that bit into a candy instead of a nut.
I just assumed you'd be against it.
But after you saved me like that, I can hardly object, can I?
Plus, I've also learned that you'll do it even if I try to stop you.
I guess. Anyway, I'd lose sleep worrying if I left you to your own devices.
Besides... To put it in your terms, I don't exactly hate you. And your cooking is good.
So that's how I feel about it,  and you're okay still working with me, right?
For now, our enemy is Caster.
She's protected by Kuzuki,  a close-combat fighter, and Archer, who's gone over to her side.
And it's only a matter of time before Saber falls under her control.
Yeah, once Saber's resistance wears out, we really won't have any chance.
Exactly. Do you have any ideas?
Hear me out, and don't get mad.
Could we work with other Masters?
It's all right. Actually, I was thinking the same thing.
We still don't know who Lancer's Master is, so that's out, but we might have a shot with Illyasviel.
How do we find her, though?
I have an idea of where she might be.
My father told me something long ago.
He said that the Einzberns have a villa in the forest outside of town.
Why can I not find it?
There is no Holy Grail here.
No. That can't possibly be true.
The Holy Grail War's overseer would never let the catalysthis trump cardout of sight.
It is my great honor to be able to welcome
a great pioneer of magecraft, the Princess of Colchis.
Now, do you have any questions?
I have been summoned by the Holy Grail
and brought back to life in this era with you as my Master.
Yes, that is what a Servant is.
And that is the Holy Grail War.
That's a mage Servant for you.
I'm glad I don't have to explain everything.
Oh, would you care for a drink?
After all, coming from more than 3,000 years is a long way.
I'm sure you must be tired.
Or would you like a bath first?
I appreciate your thoughtfulness, but before that...
you have not yet told me your name.
I'm a Master sent here by the Mages Association.
My reasons for winning the Grail are the growth of the magical world and securing a quiet future.
What do you mean by "a quiet future"?
A world where there are none who threaten me.
It's not as bad as it was in your time, but humans are still as stupid as ever.
The greater the self-defense measures, the better.
Something like that dragon Noble Phantasm of yours, for instance.
Hang on, Caster. What's that Noble Phantasm?
The summoning of a dragon from the age of myths...
I thought that's what the Noble Phantasm of Princess Medea was?
My Noble Phantasm is a conceptual one, given shape by my nature.
Even though I possess the knowledge to summon a dragon, I would not be able to control it.
Well, isn't that a shame! She can't even use a dragon!
And your Noble Phantasm is Spell-breaking...
Oh, Princess Medea was the first case of fratricide, wasn't she?
For a woman who's done nothing but betray others... ...isn't that oath-breaking dagger very fitting?
But I won't cast you aside, Caster.
As long as you remain a clever woman, I'll break you in properly.
My family is still new to the Mages' Association.
So one reason I'm fighting in this Grail War is to gain prestige.
El-Melloi didn't take the last war seriously, but I'm different.
For one thing, I've invested a lot more capital.
Do you think a purchased title is purchased glory?
No. One should use every tool at one's disposal.
If you intend to use wealth as a weapon, I'm sure there are strategies tailored to that.
As a mage, I've made preparations to overwhelm the other Masters.
Come. I'll prove it to you.
My family uses a magic system that generates mana via offerings.
Well, it's a primitive curse that relies on human sacrifice.
This workshop is a more modern and efficient version  of the original system.
I'll make one to show you.
It works best when the raw materials are fresh.
How's that? Ordinarily this would take a month to create, but I did it in the blink of an eye.
Oh, and don't worry about the raw materials.
I won't procure them in Fuyuki.
Using all these lives to create such a tiny crystal  is the act of a third-rate mage.
How could you create mana from an empty kiln?
Oh. So this appears empty to the eyes of you modern mages?
Your mana-generating technique must be one level
no, a whole world below mine.
I devoted all I had to designing this workshop  for the purpose of omitting the incantation process.
The transmutation incantation alone  is supposed to take three days and nights!
I have no need for incantations.
For me, magic is simply something to command.
Forgive me for acting out of turn,  but I ask that you close this workshop.
As a mage, I cannot abide a workshop that generates such a loss.
Ah, it would appear that I have failed to grasp the true nature of a Servant.
By my Command Spell, I order you:
do not use your Noble Phantasm on me.
I wouldn't want to be stabbed in the back by a treacherous witch.
Witch? He called me a witch?
Everyone I meet calls me a witch.
You say that Caster is too much for you to handle?
It's not a matter of ability but of trust.
Her sense of values is just too different from ours.
She is a woman who can cast magic with a wave of her fingers.
To her, human life is as worthless as paper.
After all, this woman killed her rival in love  by burning her alive in her castle.
I'd have to be crazy to trust her.
That is how you have interpreted the stories of Princess Medea?
My job is to accommodate the Masters' wishes as best I can.
All the more so for those with the Mages' Association's backing.
At this stage, the Grail has selected five Masters.
I was hoping you'd say that!
It's possible for me to make a pact with a different Servant, right?
But before that, something must be done about the Servant  to whom you are currently bound.
No matter how gifted she might be in magic, she's nothing but a vixen whose only trick is deceiving men.
Still, better safe than sorry, Father Kotomine.
I want you to give this to Lancer's Master.
She owes me at least this much as a  fellow Mages' Association participant.
Oh, it's only a contract selling the right to dispose of Caster.
If she agrees, I'll be rid of Caster  without having to waste a Command Spell.
Neither of them has any luck at all.
What is the meaning of this?
I took it upon myself to dismantle your workshop.
I shall take you to a more suitable place for fortification.
I still had around fifty left.
They were unnecessary, so I freed them.
Then what is this "more suitable" location?
The heart of this ritual. The place where the Greater Grail rests.
I have located a natural fortress that repels Servants.
If you do as I say, I shall take you there, Master.
I no longer require your services, Medea.
I order you by my Command Spell:
What's going on? It takes more than one?
I once again order you by my Command Spell:
What a foolish Master you are.
Have you forgotten what my Noble Phantasm is?
But I used a Command Spell to forbid you from using it!
Indeed, I cannot use it on you.
Thus, I used it on myself to sever my pact with you.
To you Servants, that's tantamount to suicide!
You won't be able to maintain your physical form!
You are about to die here, so is that any of your concern?
What is this? What's going on?
I won't let it end like this!
The Grail War hasn't even started!
I haven't fought a single battle!
In the end, is this how I shall die once again?
Passed around for others' convenience, exploited, reviled as a traitor...
was to return to my homeland.
You believe such an outrageous story?
I don't think you'd have any reason to lie...
unless you stand to gain something by deceiving me.
Rather, it is you who has no reason  to help a woman covered in blood.
I could hardly ascertain your character  while you were unconscious.
You need what you called a "vessel," correct?
I thought your only chance was for me to become your Master.
Go for wool and come home shorn, huh?
I see that even a peerless witch is surprisingly delicate.
I thought I told you to keep watch outside.
Oh, about that. There are no enemies worth mentioning outside.
I could no longer stand the boredom.
The moment you changed sides, Berserker became our only enemy.
Did you not side with me because you knew that?
Perhaps. Haven't you even thought that I simply wanted to sever my pact with that Master?
That I didn't care who my Master was, if not that girl?
I see. We as Servants are usually dissatisfied with our Masters.
Are you saying that you are relieved at being freed from babysitting that little girl?
Don't assume that all Servants are like you.
You do not need to tell me that.
Twisted Masters summon twisted Heroic Spirits because of their nature.
Then it makes sense that such a witch
I do not care what you think.
Your life is in my hands.
Bear that in mind when you speak.
Then, like the faithful Servant I am, I shall strive to meet the expectations of my Lord.
Just a little longer, and the Holy Grail will be in my grasp.
For now, I guess we have to pin our hopes on Illyasviel.
Berserker is definitely Caster's natural enemy.
Is Caster somehow connected to Berserker?
He said Berserker's true identity is Heracles.
If Caster really is the peerless witch Medea, they should have met on the Argo.
It's like my sore spot when it comes to Kirei.
Everyone has someone they just can't deal with.
Hey, Shirou. Would you mind walking ahead a bit?
I knew it. It seems her control extends to the entire forest.
But that means we just tripped her security system!
I don't think it's a problem, do you?
We came here to talk, not attack.
So it's better to let her know we don't intend to fight.
Now that brat's really done it!
I know I heard her laugh just now!
She walked right into my trap.
Rin's really amusing.  You can always expect an instant reaction from her.
But I wonder if they'll get here safely.
Maybe I should disable a few of the traps.
Mistress, surely you don't intend to welcome those people in.
They said that they're here to talk.
There are things I'd like to ask him.
Even if they're planning something,  they're no match for Berserker.
As that may be, I can't condone this.
If the lady of the castle says to welcome them in, you do it!
That's all the more reason for you to drive them off!
As the Einzbern princess,  you must send a proper invitation
and then throw an evening party,  in keeping with proper decorum!
Also, what you describe is not what she meant.
In that case, you two go and bring them here.
I'm telling you to go capture them!
How about it? Do we need this?
It's only natural that as maids, if we see wrongdoing, we'll exact punishment.
I guess it's an unwelcomed guest.
That jerk, dragging me along with him!
Is this really where Berserker is?!
No, he seems like a harmless fly.
Let's deal with him and be on our way.
You two... Are you Einzbern servants?
You've come at just the right time.
We have no time to deal with an unexpected guest like you.
Either leap from the roof and run away, or fall to this weapon.
You have ten seconds to decide.
Four, three, two, one. Are you kidding me?!
What have we here? Homunculi, eh?
Even though you are humans only in shape, you function as children of nature.
They must have used a fine mold to make you.
Don't worry about me. Just get away.
I shall pardon your disrespect, given your display of awe.
If you value your lives, be gone from my sight.
I shall grant you ten seconds in appreciation for allowing my Master to escape.
Then we cannot do as you ask.
Our purpose is to protect our mistress from all outside threats.
Though you strike me as royalty, we cannot allow a man who reeks so strongly of blood to pass!
Is that so? Then fall like flowers.
I expect that the Grail's vessel will come running  at the sound of your screams.
Shirou is coming here, to the castle where Mother once stayed.
The mages never learn, do they?
One should never give a tool a human heart.
Humans are incapable of reciprocating your purity.
As long as I draw breath...
I will not let you near my mistress.
Then you may see your duty through to the last.
You are the doll that possesses the Grail vessel?
I see that crossing a human and a homunculus  has given rise to a peculiarity.
Toying with you will relieve my boredom.
Shall we reenact a battle of legend here?
No way! Those were all Noble Phantasms?
because he's the strongest in the world!
Strolling in through the front door would be a bad idea.
Shirou, we'll go in that way!
So that is how it is.
No way! Those were all Noble Phantasms?
What the hell, man? You're crazy powerful!
Compared to that, this guy was all bark and no bite.
This is why I can't stand meat-heads!
If you value your life, stand back, fool.
It is far too early for laughter.
I have long since grown jaded to the sight of heroes that do not fall when cut or burned.
But I have never seen a man truly return from the dead.
It would seem your life and legends  have taken shape as a Noble Phantasm.
That Noble Phantasm is the one asset I lack.
In that sense, I suppose even I stand at a disadvantage.
Though it vexes me, it seems only the highest class of arms will work on that man.
It is said that Heracles overcame twelve penances
and was welcomed to the ranks of the gods afterward.
He is truly indomitable the ultimate expression of human perseverance.
My treasury, however, is the exact opposite.
It is infinitethe ultimate expression of overwhelming force.
As you can see, it overflows with weaponry to slay heroes.
Fight me in earnest, or every last one of your labors will be for naught.
because he's the strongest in the world!
killed at the hands of the man she loved above all others.
Mother said that she would become the Holy Grail and Kiritsugu would keep her safe.
You were... We were betrayed by that man.
And cast aside like mere tools.
You're lying... You're lying! You must be!
Everything you're saying must be a lie!
I'll be okay... I can manage on my own.
They say that the traitor died.
They say he went and died, never once thinking to come back for us.
I don't care. That has nothing to do with me.
I've decided to live my life by myself.
But it has everything to do with you.
You see, he had a child.
That man had a family. A family other than me.
Yes. I know you'll be able to kill each other.
You'll be able to kill each other soon.
After all, the Greater Grail's flame was not extinguished.
The battle ended without resolution, so it will soon resume.
That gives you a reason to live, just like that human, right?
It hurts... It hurts... I don't want to do this anymore.
Why does my body have to be opened up every day?
They should just quit that stupid Holy Grail War.
We cannot. After all, it is our duty.
The miracle that occurred a thousand years ago...
We were created in order to replicate it.
That will only bring happiness to humans.
We have no concept of happiness, for we are mere tools. We are the used, not the users.
Even Elder Acht has probably never experienced joy.
Yes. We are all nothing but tools to activate the Holy Grail.
To that end, we have suffered for a thousand years.
And then, they finally achieved you.
Yes. You are the Einzberns' crowning achievement
the fruit of the techniques that created us.
No matter how much time passes, they will never be able to create one that surpasses you.
So if you are defeated, they will all give up.
Elder Acht will probably turn off the power source himself.
For they will have their answer:
that we are relics of the past.
You'll all end your own lives?
Yes, the factory known as the Einzberns
will abandon their thousand years of research.
With smiles on their faces, they will concede that they gave it their best,  but it was all for naught.
You're all alive! Why do you have to die?
I'm the one who's gonna fight!  Shouldn't I be the one to die?!
Do not mourn us, sweet child.
Even if everything was for nothing, we do not mind.
Even if we cannot be saved, we will finally be freed of our obligations.
Duty, duty... It's always about our duty!
Who do the Einzberns think they are?
We never had identities of our own!
I am Sella, and starting today, I will be looking after you.
And this is Leysritt, who has been assigned to protect you.
Please forgive her. Leysritt is still being fine-tuned
Yes, the summoning has already been performed.
He is the great hero of Greek myth, Heracles.
With a Heroic Spirit such as this, your victory is assured!
We place our lives and our meager abilities at your
No, thank you. I don't need anything of the sort.
Servants are nothing more than tools.
It doesn't matter who they are.
I can manage just fine on my own.
I'll win the Holy Grail War by myself.
Don't make me laugh. Servants are just familiars that are bound by rules.
If not for my Command Spells, it would betray me in an instant.
We will now begin linking you to Berserker.
Seventy percent of your body is composed of magic circuits, so you will receive far more Servant feedback than an ordinary Master.
And you call yourself the most powerful Heroic Spirit?
Let's perform the contract ritual another time!
I'll tame him soon enough, so be quiet and watch.
I'm the most powerful Master in the world!
Oh, right. I was in the middle of the final test.
If I make it back to the castle alive, I can go to Fuyuki.
When I get back to the castle, I'll just summon a new Servant.
I'll summon one that won't cause me pain and isn't so scary.
Because you don't want to make me suffer?
Because you don't want to hurt me?
You didn't protect me because I ordered you to  or because you're a Servant.
You've been protecting me of your own free will, haven't you?
Berserker won't lose to the likes of him.
No matter what happens, don't get involved.
We have no way to fight right now.
Got it? If you want to save people, save yourself first, and then think about others.
How about it? Since you will die anyway, why not lay down your burden at the end?
If you fight unencumbered,  you still have a chance of slaying me.
In that case, I shall impose upon you the greatest of labors!
